<doc id="323761" wikidata="Q2544034" url="?curid=323761" title="Phyllodactylus">
<text>Phyllodactylus is a genus of geckos distributed in South America and Central America, and as far north as the southern United States. They are commonly known as &quot;leaf-toed geckos&quot; in their native range, and otherwise as American leaf-toed geckos to distinguish them from unrelated genera with similar feet.
==Species==
&quot;Phyllodactylus&quot; contains these species:

*&quot;Phyllodactylus andysabini&quot; – Andy Sabin&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko, Wolf Volcano leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus angustidigitus&quot; – narrow leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus apricus&quot; – Las Animas Island gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus barringtonensis&quot; – Barrington leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus baurii&quot; – Baur&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus benedettii&quot; 
*&quot;Phyllodactylus bordai&quot; – Guerreran leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus bugastrolepis&quot; – Catalina Island leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus cleofasensis&quot; 
*&quot;Phyllodactylus clinatus&quot; – Cerro Illescas gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus coronatus&quot; – Coronado Island leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus darwini&quot; – Darwin&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus davisi&quot; – Davis&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus delcampoi&quot; – Del Campo&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus delsolari&quot; 
*&quot;Phyllodactylus dixoni&quot; – Dixon&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus duellmani&quot; – Duellman&#x27;s pigmy leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus duncanensis&quot; 
*&quot;Phyllodactylus galapagensis&quot; – Galapagos leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus gerrhopygus&quot; – South American leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus gilberti&quot; – Gilbert&#x27;s leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus gorii&quot; - Española leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus hispaniolae&quot; – Dominican leaf-toed gecko
*&quot;Phyllodactylus homolepidurus&quot; – Sonoran leaf-toed gecko
