<doc id="323766" wikidata="Q2298536" url="?curid=323766" title="Tarentola">
<text>Tarentola is a genus of geckos, commonly known as wall geckos.

They are native to lands on both sides of the Atlantic Ocean; on the western side they can be found in the West Indies, while on the eastern side they can be found in mainland Africa, Macaronesia, and the Mediterranean region. However, some species such as &quot;T. mauritanica&quot; have been introduced worldwide.

==Classification of genus &quot;Tarentola&quot;==

The following species and subspecies are recognized as being valid.
*&quot;Tarentola albertschwartzi&quot; – Jamaican giant gecko (possibly extinct)
*&quot;Tarentola americana&quot; – American wall gecko
**&quot;Tarentola americana americana&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola americana warreni&quot; – Warren&#x27;s American wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola angustimentalis&quot; – Canary wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola annularis&quot; – ringed wall gecko 
**&quot;Tarentola annularis annularis&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola annularis relicta&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola boavistensis&quot; – Boavista wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola bocagei&quot; – Bocage&#x27;s wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola boehmei&quot; – Morocco wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola boettgeri&quot; – Boettger&#x27;s wall gecko
**&quot;Tarentola boettgeri boettgeri&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola boettgeri bischoffi&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola boettgeri hierrensis&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola caboverdiana&quot; – Cape Verde wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola chazaliae&quot; – helmethead gecko
*&quot;Tarentola crombiei&quot; – wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola darwini&quot; – Darwin&#x27;s wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola delalandii&quot; – Tenerife wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola deserti&quot; – desert wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola ephippiata&quot; – African wall gecko
**&quot;Tarentola ephippiata ephippiata&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola ephippiata nikolausi&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola fascicularis&quot; – Wolfgang&#x27;s wall gecko, moorish gecko
*&quot;Tarentola fogoensis&quot; – Fogo wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola gigas&quot; – giant wall gecko
**&quot;Tarentola gigas brancoensis&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola gigas gigas&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola gomerensis&quot; – Gomera wall gecko 
*&quot;Tarentola hoggarensis&quot; – African wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola maioensis&quot; – Maio wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola mauritanica&quot; – moorish gecko
**&quot;Tarentola mauritanica juliae&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola mauritanica mauritanica&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola mauritanica pallida&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola mindiae&quot; – Qattara gecko
*&quot;Tarentola neglecta&quot; – Algerian wall gecko 
**&quot;Tarentola neglecta geyri&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola neglecta lanzai&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola neglecta neglecta&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola nicolauensis&quot; – São Nicolau wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola panousei&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola parvicarinata&quot; – Sierra Leone wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola pastoria&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola protogigas&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola protogigas hartogi&quot; 
**&quot;Tarentola protogigas protogigas&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola raziana&quot; – Raso wall gecko
*&quot;Tarentola rudis&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola senegambiae&quot; 
*&quot;Tarentola substituta&quot; – São Vicente wall gecko

&quot;Nota bene&quot;: A binomial authority or a trinomial authority in parentheses indicates that the species or subspecies was originally described in a genus other than &quot;Tarentola&quot;.

